Just and praiseworthy deed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- "A ceremony of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's  Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) for declaring a struggle against the U.S. war preparations and for the U.S. troop pullout from South Korea and for the building of a reunified country based on confederacy" was recently held in Pyongyang, Seoul and Tokyo in the form of a joint meeting under  an agreement of the north, south and overseas headquarters of Pomchonghakryon.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minju Joson today describes this as demonstration of the strong will of youths and students at home and abroad to keep the U.S. from igniting a war and reunify the country independently and in a peaceful way and as a  just and praiseworthy deed, which mirrors the tense situation prevailing in Korea and the desire of all the fellow countrymen for peace and peaceful reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The news analyst of the paper says:   The U.S. have left no stone unturned to swallow up the North Korea and to dominate the whole of Korea. 
   The obtaining situation proves that without efforts to foil the reckless war plan of the U.S., peace and security on the Korean peninsula cannot be preserved and the very  existence of the nation may be in danger. 
   Youths and students at home and abroad will never retreat from the struggle against the U.S. and for independence, against fascism and for democracy and national reunification, but will fight, with concerted efforts, not yielding to appeasement, deception, threat and suppression on the part of the traitorous rulers.

Reinvestigation into legal circles' irregularities demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- The Citizens' Federation for Democratic Society, the South Korean Confederation of Trade Unions and other organizations of South Korea made public statements on February 1 demanding reinvestigation into the legal circles' irregularities in Taejon in protest against the result of the prosecution's investigation, according to a radio report from Seoul.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Citizens' Federation for Democratic Society demanded resignation of senior prosecutors, a hearing on the personnel affair related to prosecutors and the introduction of special prosecutor system, saying that it is a mockery of people to give a finishing touch to investigation in such a way as accepting resignations and disciplinary measures against a few prosecutors.
   The Citizens' Federation for Economic Justice claimed that it is a violation of legal orders and justice for the lower officials' prosecution to punish only junior officials for irregularities without taking punitive actions against more guilty judges and prosecutors.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean Confederation of Trade Unions and other organizations stated: it was just the same as hitting the small fry while letting the big ones go free that only a few junior prosecutors were punished without dismissing their seniors.
   They also demanded full reinvestigation and thorough reform of judicial organs.
